[7] Rabies vaccine required globally - Comment
Date: Fri 29 Sep 2017
From: Merritt Clifton <Animals24.7@frontier.com> [edited]


Re: PRO/IN> PRO/AH/EDR> World Rabies Day 2017: eradication prospects discussed

It has been estimated that should [rabies vaccine for canines] production continue at 2015 levels, there will be a cumulative shortage of about 7.5 billion doses to meet expected demand to achieve dog rabies elimination by 2030.

On the other hand, if intensive ring vaccination is practiced in the relatively few areas where verifiable rabies cases are actually occurring, accompanied by saturation vaccination and dog sterilization in the hot zones, canine rabies should be eradicable by 2030 with the present vaccine supply, even though a much greater supply and more vaccination would be ideal.

The trick will be to accurately target the use of the available vaccines to where the most urgent need is.

--
Merritt Clifton
<Animals24.7@frontier.com>

[The author considers a possible reduction in the required quantities of the vaccine by adaptation to the actual number of rabies cases debated by him in 20151022.3735706 and 20151028.3748032. - Mod.AS

